<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4629164>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Egg of Nasusbilharzia melancorhypha n. sp. from nasal tissue of Cygnus melancoryphus collected in lake Pellegrini. Scale bar in micrometers." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4629164/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4629166>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Nasusbilharzia melancorhypha n. sp. from nasal tissue of Cygnus melancoryphus (A) anterior and posterior end of a male; (B) posterior end of a male. Scale bar in micrometers." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4629166/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4629168>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Microphotograph of Nasusbilharzia melancorhypha n. sp. obtained from nasal tissue of Cygnus melancoryphus. A. Anterior end. B. Posterior end. C. Detail of well-developed suckers. D. anterior end of gynaecophoric canal with cirrus. E. Relative positions of the ventral sucker to the start of the gynaecophoric canal. F. Gynaecophoric canal with cirrus and thickened bands. G. Gynaecophoric canal and cirrus with spines. H. detail of cirrus spines: I. Detail of tegumental spines. Scale bar in micrometers." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4629168/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4629160>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Phylogenetic trees based on Bayesian Inference of the 28S rDNA gene tree. The samples from this study are in bold and highlighted in a gray box. Nodal support is indicated by posterior probabilities (*=1.0) and GenBank accessions follow the taxon name." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4629160/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

